articles.title: Buttigieg defends Biden confusing Ukraine and Iraq twice in 2 days: 'Very focused on details'
articles.author: Fox News
articles.excerpt: Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg defended President Biden mistakenly referring to the Russia-Ukraine war as the 'war in Iraq' twice in one week.
articles.summary:
Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg defended President Biden mistakenly referring to the Russia-Ukraine war as the 'war in Iraq' twice in one week. Secretary of Transportation Pete Buttigieg dismissed President Biden repeatedly confusing the countries of Ukraine and Iraq while appearing on"CNN Primetime" Wednesday night.
The president faced intense criticism on Wednesday after suggesting that Russian President Vladimir Putin was"clearly losing the war in Iraq." Biden made a similar misstep during a fundraiser on Tuesday night when he referenced"Iraq" instead of Ukraine without correcting himself.

articles.title: Pence makes surprise trip to Ukraine, in move to set himself apart from GOP field: 'We are with you'
articles.author: Cathey
articles.excerpt: His message in Ukraine was clear: "We are with you."
articles.summary:
In a dramatic move to differentiate himself on a key foreign policy issue, former Vice President Mike Pence on Thursday made a surprise trip to Ukraine, projecting solidarity against Russia in a way, so far, unmatched by his Republican competitors.

His message in Ukraine was clear: "We are with you."

"As I made clear to President [Volodymyr] Zelenskyy today, when I return home, whatever the future holds for me and my family, we're gonna stand for freedom," Pence told reporters. "And I'll do my part to make sure that America continues to stand for the courageous fighters here in Ukraine that are fighting to reclaim their freedom.
